{"id": "issue-49765f", "title": "Ensure all skills implement search() method for universal search", "description": "The universal search functionality exists in core (src/glorious_agents/core/search.py and cli.py), but needs all skills to implement the search() method.\n\n**Current state:**\n- \u2705 Universal search command: `agent search` exists\n- \u2705 SearchResult protocol defined in core/search.py\n- \u2705 Most skills already have search() implemented:\n  - ai, cache, code-atlas, feedback, issues, notes, planner, prompts, temporal, vacuum\n\n**Required work:**\nAudit all skills and ensure each has a search() method that:\n- Returns list[SearchResult] \n- If search is not applicable for that skill, return []\n- Otherwise return relevant results with proper scoring\n\n**Skills to check:**\nRun through all example-skills/* and verify each has search() or explicitly returns []\n\n**Implementation:**\nEach skill.py should have:\n```python\ndef search(query: str, limit: int = 10) -> list[SearchResult]:\n    # If not applicable: return []\n    # Otherwise: return relevant SearchResult objects\n```", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "type": "feature", "assignee": null, "epic_id": null, "labels": ["enhancement", "new-skill", "search"], "created_at": "2025-11-15T22:02:11.277301", "updated_at": "2025-11-16T00:27:36.132824", "closed_at": "2025-11-16T00:27:36.132825", "project_id": "default"}
