{"id": "issue-c89515", "title": "Enhance 'issues show' to accept multiple issue IDs", "description": "The `issues show` command should accept multiple issue IDs as arguments.\n\n**Current behavior:**\nMust chain multiple commands: `uv run agent issues show issue-5fd36a && uv run agent issues show issue-e7b502`\n\n**Desired behavior:**\n- Accept multiple issue IDs: `uv run agent issues show issue-5fd36a issue-e7b502 issue-49765f`\n- When `--json` flag is given: return a mapping of issue-ids -> issue-data\n- When `--json` is not given: print issues in sequence with separators\n\n**Benefits:**\n- More efficient - single command invocation\n- Cleaner command chains\n- Better JSON output structure for programmatic use", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "type": "feature", "assignee": null, "epic_id": null, "labels": [], "created_at": "2025-11-16T00:20:57.470683", "updated_at": "2025-11-16T00:35:58.489004", "closed_at": "2025-11-16T00:35:58.489005", "project_id": "default"}
